Government Orders: -

As per the provisions of Section 4 (4) and 4 (5) of the Maharashtra Prevention of Delay in discharge of Government Duties and Regulation of Transfer of Government Employees Act, 2005, the following officers of the Sub-Divisional Magistrate cadre have been posted in front of their name on administrative grounds / request in Column No. The post indicated in section 4 is being posted with the approval of the competent authority in the interest of public service and administrative convenience.

The aforesaid Deputy Collector is being unilaterally relieved from his present office with effect from the date 18.03.2025 (M.No.) for joining the post of Secretary. The date on which the officer concerned appeared in place of the new appointment should be immediately communicated to the Government by e-mail / post at e2.revenue@maharashtra.gov.in.

The officers concerned shall be such as may be prescribed under Rule 15 of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Period of assumption of office, non-acceptance of service and remuneration during periods of suspension, dismissal and removal from service) Rules, 1981.
